== dirs on an empty stack shows only the current directory:
D
== pushd builds the stack, current first:
D/a D
D/b D/a D
D/b D/a D
== dirs -v numbers each entry from the top:
0  D/b
1  D/a
2  D
== popd returns through the stack:
D/a D
D
PWD=D
== pushd with no argument swaps the top two:
D D/a
PWD=D
== pushd +1 rotates the Nth entry to the top:
D/a D D/b
PWD=D/a
== popd +1 drops a saved entry without a chdir:
D/b D
D/b D
PWD=D/b
== dirs -c clears the stack:
D/a
== the home directory abbreviates to ~:
~/a ~
== popd on an empty stack reports an error:
error: popd found the directory stack empty.
     1 |  cd 'D'; popd
       |                            ^~~~ here.
note: Push a directory first with `pushd DIR`.
